00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:28.000
We came from the television industry,

00:00:28.320 --> 00:00:31.160
and we found that some content wasn’t suited for TV

00:00:31.160 --> 00:00:32.600
or wasn’t done on TV the way we would like.

00:00:32.640 --> 00:00:36.080
It also had to do with trying new communication formats

00:00:36.080 --> 00:00:37.600
and new audiovisual languages.

00:00:37.600 --> 00:00:41.360
On the internet this didn’t happen; you could explore, you could try new ways of communicating.,

00:00:59.480 --> 00:01:02.720
If you say something and it doesn’t bother anyone, then you haven’t said anything.

00:01:02.760 --> 00:01:05.200
You don’t have to be afraid when coming up with new content,

00:01:05.200 --> 00:01:08.120
of offending or provoking someone.

00:01:08.160 --> 00:01:12.440
You just make it, you know? And that’s when you’ll see where your audience is,

00:01:12.480 --> 00:01:13.880
who you connect with and who you don’t.

00:01:13.920 --> 00:01:16.240
Whenever you want to say something

00:01:16.280 --> 00:01:19.080
there will be someone somewhere who wants to listen to it,

00:01:19.080 --> 00:01:22.160
someone that had the same thought as you, or that has the same interest that you do…

